{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"47784887-ff88-4e41-8dc2-86d7d2b84ed6","content":"There's no pipeline file in the current directory, so here's a general guide for the migration:\n\n### Key changes\n\n1. **Replace `VSTest@3` with `DotNetCoreCLI@2`** (or a plain `dotnet test` script step). Microsoft.Testing.Platform runs via `dotnet test` — VSTest@3 doesn't support it.\n\n2. **Enable TRX output** with `--logger trx` (or the MSBuild property).\n\n3. **Enable code coverage** with `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` or Coverlet.\n\n### Before (VSTest@3)\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\n### After (dotnet test)\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --logger trx\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Project-side prerequisites\n\nIn each test `.csproj`, ensure:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Notes\n- **`PublishTestResults@2`** is now required — VSTest@3 auto-published, but `dotnet test` does not.\n- **`condition: always()`** ensures results publish even on test failure.\n- For Coverlet instead of the VS collector, use `--collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"` and point `PublishCodeCoverageResults` at the Cobertura XML.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f8c4da53-739c-4f2b-9768-0036a97d17aa","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no YAML files in the repository. The user is asking a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":633,"requestId":"7C1F:DF52E:27431B7:2B4AA8A:69F93EF5"},"id":"41d77e29-9182-44e4-be60-92d4d3c67baa","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:51:15.323Z","parentId":"9c05358f-5e83-4559-a120-129927eba6d0"}
